subsection.def:
animal
                    (動物) includes reptiles, but does not include
                birds or fish;

bath
                    (浴、沐浴)
                includes shower bath and turkish bath;

cemetery
                    (墳場) means any place for the time being
                specified in the Fifth Schedule;

cream
                    (忌廉) means that part of milk rich in fat
                which has been separated by skimming or otherwise;

paragraph.content:
the presence in any building of any fire service installation or
                        equipment which from lack of proper maintenance or for any other reason is
                        not in efficient working order;

any person who sells to or seeks orders from any person who is a dealer
                        in any such goods, wares or merchandise and who buys to sell again;
                        or

subsection.def:
licensee
                    (持牌人) includes a delegate appointed pursuant
                to a requirement under the provisions of section 125(7);

paragraph.content:
any mud, clay, brick, stone, plaster, sand, cement, concrete, mortar,
                        wood, timber, sawdust, plastic, construction material or excavated
                        material;

subsection.def:
mortuary
                    (殮房) means any premises or place set apart or
                habitually used for the reception, storage or treatment of human remains;

petroleum
                    (石油) means crude petroleum or any oil made
                from petroleum or from coal, shale, peat or other bituminous substances;

vault
                    (墓穴) includes underground burial places of
                every description, except graves;

paragraph.content:
where the site is owned by the Government, the person who has been
                        appointed the contractor in respect of the site, if he has entered on the
                        site at the relevant time;

subsection.def:
owners’ corporation (業主立案法團), in relation to a building (or part of a
                building), means the corporation registered under section 8 of Cap. 344 for the building (or part of the
                building);

person in charge (負責人) means—(a)in relation to any premises that are common parts of a
                        building—(i)the owners’ corporation for the building (or part of the building);
                            or(ii)if there is no such owners’ corporation—the owner of the premises;
                            or(b)in relation to any other premises or a vessel—(i)the occupier of the premises or vessel; or(ii)the owner of the premises or vessel. (Added 13 of 2025 s. 5)

paragraph.content:
for imposing requirements as to, and otherwise regulating, the labelling,
                    marking or advertising of food intended for sale for human consumption or drugs
                    intended for sale for use by man, and the descriptions which may be applied to
                    such food or drugs;

subsection.def:
business (業務) has
                the meaning given by section 2(1) of the Business Registration Ordinance
                    (Cap. 310);

paragraph.content:
in respect of any land managed or controlled by the Housing Authority
                        established by the Housing Ordinance (Cap.
                        283), the Housing Authority;

unless the removal or disposal referred to in that subsection is, in the
                    opinion of the Chief Executive in Council, necessary in the public interest;
                    and

section.def:
Board
                (委員會) means the Licensing Appeals Board
            established under section 125A;

Chairman
                (主席) means the person appointed to that office
            under section 125A(2);

secretary
                (秘書) means the secretary to the Board appointed
            under section 125I(1);

paragraph.content:
for the purpose of taking any action, or executing any work, authorized or
                    required by the provisions of this Ordinance to be taken or executed by the
                    authorizing authority;

a reference to “between the hours of 7 a.m. and 7 p.m.” in subsection (1)
                    is to be construed as a reference to “between the hours of 7 a.m. and 10
                    p.m.”;

a reference to the occupier of any premises in subsections (1) and (2) is
                    to be construed as a reference to the owner or occupier of the premises;
                    and

subsection.def:
Chairman
                    (主席) means the Chairman of the Appeal Board
                appointed under section 128D(3);

premises
                    (處所) includes any place, vessel and any part
                of a place or vessel;

